INR0hePbJbiL1LGp8_fHXzYnTv-vab6FFQQx8=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Testing lock behavior**\\n\\nI see that the existing test works, but I’m considering whether I should directly test with the circularity lock acquired. I could assert the lock behavior by applying it twice, but it seems tricky without direct reflection. I wonder if there’s a potential issue with the class name length. Alright, I’ll proceed to write a new file and ensure that the package is not a library package. Let’s keep moving forward!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Zp2Pe6GGzbdBHY8sMpsQDJtD|fc_03cd2d6afd763dc2016a29831cca1481909d819e0d029e969d", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/AgentBuilderInnerDescriptionStrategyInnerSuperTypeLoadingInnerUnlockingClassLoadingDelegateTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_projectreactor_tools.blockhound;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent.builder.AgentBuilder;\nimport reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.description.type.TypeDescription;\nimport reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.pool.TypePool;\nimport reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.utility.JavaModule;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Modifier;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class AgentBuilderInnerDescriptionStrategyInnerSuperTypeLoadingInnerUnlockingClassLoadingDelegateTest {\n    @Test\n    void loadsSuperTypeWhileTemporarilyReleasingCircularityLock() {\n        ClassLoader classLoader = Child.class.getClassLoader();\n        assertThat(classLoader).isNotNull();\n\n        AgentBuilder.CircularityLock circularityLock = new AgentBuilder.CircularityLock.Default();\n        assertThat(circularityLock.acquire()).isTrue();\n\n        AgentBuilder.DescriptionStrategy descriptionStrategy =\n                new AgentBuilder.DescriptionStrategy.SuperTypeLoading(new LatentChildDescriptionStrategy());\n        TypeDescription childDescription = descriptionStrategy.apply(\n                Child.class.getName(),\n                null,\n                TypePool.Empty.INSTANCE,\n                circularityLock,\n                classLoader,\n                JavaModule.ofType(Child.class));\n\n        TypeDescription superClass = childDescription.getSuperClass().asErasure();\n\n        assertThat(superClass.represents(Parent.class)).isTrue();\n        assertThat(circularityLock.acquire()).isFalse();\n        circularityLock.release();\n    }\n\n    private static final class LatentChildDescriptionStrategy implements AgentBuilder.DescriptionStrategy {\n        @Override\n        public boolean isLoadedFirst() {\n            return false;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public TypeDescription apply(\n                String typeName,\n                Class<?> type,\n                TypePool typePool,\n                AgentBuilder.CircularityLock circularityLock,\n                ClassLoader classLoader,\n                JavaModule module) {\n            return new TypeDescription.Latent(\n                    typeName,\n                    Modifier.PUBLIC,\n                    TypeDescription.Generic.OfNonGenericType.ForLoadedType.of(Parent.class));\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static class Parent {\n    }\n\n    private static final class Child extends Parent {\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1699, "output": 695, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30042, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781105430943, "responseId": "resp_03cd2d6afd763dc2016a2983179